I have come to the conclusion that college makes people pretensiously 'deep.'  I have come out of livejournal hiatus to share that piece of wisdom with the community.

Your Birthdate: March 15
You take life as it is, and you find happiness in a variety of things. You tend to be close to family and friends. But it's hard to get into your inner circle. Making the little things wonderful is important to you, and you probably have an inviting home. You seek harmony with others, but occasionally you have a very stubborn streak. Your strength: Your intense optimism Your weakness: You shy away from exploring your talents Your power color: Jade Your power symbol: Flower Your power month: June

I really love the way whenever my mom takes my car, she always parks it facing out because she knows I don't like backing out of spots.  And I love that she always likes to talk to me, even when I'm mean to her.

I really love the way whenever one of us writes something on the white board in the kitchen, my dad always adds something dumb to it.  And I love the way he laughs very hard at his own goofy jokes.

I love that I have no doubt that if a crisis should come about, Sara can be trusted, hands down, to take control.  And I love that we're finally starting to really get along.

I love that Kate is my best friend.  Enough said.

I love that Dan is alot like me, and I can almost always tell what he's thinking and I know he's good a really great head on his shoulders. 

I really appreciate these guys and I love my family.

i wonder if people really believe that words filled with thoughtful inspiration and encouragement really mean something.  i mean have you ever really broken down some deep, complicated thing someone tells you to try to make you feel better and just think to yourself "that is totally ridiculous and insanely cliche"? because i, for one, do that an awful lot.  its a good idea to think before you speak and to remember that the simplest things mean the most.  honestly sometimes people baffle me.  and not always in a bad way, just in general.  i really feel like some people use the awe-inspiring quotes to make themselves look so wise and intelligent when really they have no idea what they're talking about, they just want you to think that they're so helpful and smart and blather blather.  or maybe im wrong and they know what they're talking about and they know who other people are and who they are.  and i just dont know who i am.  sometimes i wish that there was a test or someone you could talk to that could just tell you right off the bat who you are.  but then i think maybe it just comes in stages.  maybe thats the point because if you knew who you were all at once, where would you go from there?  look at me, im just a philosopher.  ha. oh well.  the chronicles of narnia was fabulous.

do you ever feel stuck? i mean honest to God, panic inducingly stuck with no real idea about why you're feeling it at that exact moment or how you can stop it?  i cannot stand that feeling and i keep getting it more and more.  i dont know what it is but right now, in this moment, i have no clue what im doing.  not just right now, but in general.  what am i doing?  im just waking up and going through the motions and really accomplishing much in terms of relationships or life plans or anything productive.  and i dont know WHAT to do.  i dont know how to change how i feel, or who i am, or what im doing.  i dont know, or maybe i just dont want to, make things different.  i do and i dont, i want them to be different but i dont know how to actually make them different. 

sometimes i feel like i have so much to say but no one to tell it to without hurting peoples feelings, or making them feel uncomfortable, or making myself feel to vulnerable.  im ultimately always disappointed when i try to confide in people because i never get the reactions that i expect, or hope for.  i dont know what the deal is and its my fault alot of the time.  i make a big deal about people not listening to me but maybe thats because im not always willing to talk.  this doesnt even make any sense.  sometimes i feel so alone that i really cant even breathe and how ridiculous does that sound but its true.  and im not special because everyone has the same problems all the time everyday all around the world, and worse, and i am honestly running a complainathon.  good.    sometimes i really wish to just not be anywhere.  im such a frikkin baby.

im not a nice person anymore and thats not a good thing and i need to change it.  i shouldnt make fun of people just  because it makes my friends laugh.  i shouldnt really make fun of people, period, and i dont like myself for doing it.  im sorry to everyone and i absolutely refuse to be part of any drama at all.  i am almost 20, its time for drama to end.  so im just gonna be neutral from now on.  or try anyway.  no more cutting ties because im not good at it and i dont like it and then i feel like a horrible person when it gets put back together.  i need to start thinking before i speak.  and being nice to everyone.  happy advent.
i think you are cute.  talk to me sometime.  the end.
i wish that i was pretty. and confident. just because i feel like that would change alot of things. i think it would make things better. hows that for superficial.

i am simply updating this piece because im tired of looking at the saddish posts.  i do not want people to think that im a complainmonger which this journal makes me seem like.  i dont think that sentence was at all gramatically correct. also probably complainmonger isnt a word but i like it anyway.  yea so anyway, i really only use this journal to vent and i dont usually vent about good stuff so you know the dilly. 

in a nut shell i like some people and do not like other people and i am probably going to spend a MAD long time in purgatory...theoretically of course because i dont really believe in purgatory but whatevah.  i really like my ipod shuffle and i really liked corpse bride. it was a good movie.  not as funny as some people thought (devon. haha) but it was fantastic anyway.  i cannot WAIT until harry potter comes out it looks stunning.  lets talk about my jewish holiday! i worked on tuesday and then we went to cheesecake factory.  it was very good.  a bricket is a nut, you can take it off if youd like.  ha stelluttttttttttti.  and then wedensday (i still dont know how to spell that) was just work and i worked with devbo YAY FOR DEVONNY BALONEYY.  and then i went to my sisters gameeeee and then i ate and now im here. i hate when people give a blow by blow, its silly.  but i just did it because when i do it its cool.

its weird and bad that im not as done with you as i thought i was.  maybe im a really selfish person and i just havent noticed it yet. i swear i dont know anything.

it's remarkable how much you can overestimate somebody.  little things are important, but they are not enough to cover you're entire personality.  when the good things are few and far between its probably time to say enough is enough.  but its disheartening because i would love to believe that people are good and that people care, but it is really getting more and more difficult to believe that.  i think im coming to terms with it and accepting it but that might just be making me cynical, which i really dont want to happen.  and its amazing how little someone can really know you, and its all because they just dont care enough to ask.  maybe you're bursting to talk but nobody will ask.  society is pretty self centered.  it's good to be concerned with yourself so you dont get trampled but you need to open your eyes and see that -holy cow- there are other people on the planet.  sometimes i feel so stuck and trapped and alone that i think my heart is literally going to break apart.  luckily/unfortunately the moments are often fleeting and i push it to the back of my head, or my stomach, and i wouldnt be suprised if one day i woke up with an ulcer or a complete mental explosion.  the price we pay to be peoples sound boards.  people talk to me because i listen without fail because thats who i am but who knows, maybe i just wont anymore.  i think people should be a little bit more naive because we're all too smart and sharp for our own good.  ignorance is bliss and life is what happens when we're busy making plans.  life isnt a series of momentous moments; it is what it is, its happening now, later, before.  why does everything have to be so calculated and such a tremendous deal.  howcome we cant just relax sometimes and go slow.  everything is so fast paced and important.  why can i not find anybo(d)y that will appreciate and like and love me.  oh because im waiting for (h)i[t](m) to fall out of the sky because im not brave enough to do anything for myself.  but i would love to know from somebody that im not very unattractive.  i cant make any decisions or any friends because im complacent and trying my hardest to be oblivous to my stagnant state of being.  i give myself too much credit and not enough.  i like the fact that im the only one whose going to read this, and that thought was one of the most unsarcastic things ive ever written, even if it looks facecious.  its amazing how people change but we all miss it, unless if directly affects us, because we're primarily concerned with ourselves.  my mom and dad know me better than anyone in the world and that makes me sad sometimes because i know what they know about me makes them sad and i would rather feel it alone because i dont ever want them to blame themselves because its not their fault.  i could take/write forever about everything and nothing but its generally unimportant and i think things become too scientific and less real when people try to analyze them so much.  i appreciate simplicity and i think it speaks a whole lot louder than anything "profound" i would love to be simple, maybe i am i just dont know who to ask or how to find out.  i wish that the world was more innocent and less dramatic and kinder.  or i wish i could meet the people that were.  i have lots more to say. maybe someday i'll say them.
life makes me so nervous that im finding it increasingly difficult to breathe. have a good day, please! sincerely yours, an on y mous. ;) lessthanthree.

i hate that the fact that im not really good at anything.  im good at things, just not really good at anything in particular.  and i hate the fact that there used to be something i thought i was pretty good at, and then someone else just blows me out of the water.  someone who's really good at other things, but is really good at this too.  and i hate that i was proud of the thing i was good at, and the person who's better at it just brushes it aside because it comes to naturally to them.  i wish something came naturally to me, but i guess we cant all be that lucky.  im just here. im not serving any special purpose. im not really good at anything.  i dont change people.  i dont change.  everyone else changes and i stay the same, only i get more jealous and angry the more other people change.  im not permanent to anyone but my family.  im filled with sunshine today, obviously.
if there is a way to be less jealous and more content with my deal, id love to know it.  for serious. i miss high school

so in a nutshell, i got every single dingle class i wanted when i registered last night.  it took me like 2 minutes and BAM i was done.  WHAT NOW? SUCK IT HOFSTRA, YOU CANT HOLD ME DOWN, ACADEMICALLY OR OTHERWISE.  im so thrilled.  as is devon.  holler for last names starting with g and h.

check it outtttt. im writing in this peice when i clearly have much more important things to do with my sparse amount of time.  I LOVE IT.  i SHOULD be studying for my bio test because it is tomorrow.  i thought i would have a good 3 hours to study tomorrow but no, hofstra just NEEDS students who work on campus to go to a stupid boring stupid something about jobs that i dont even know what it is.  im pumped.  i know how to answer the phone, i know how to type crap, i know how to talk to people.. usually.  please leave me BEEEEEEEEEEE.  today was my long class day. i hate tuesdays.  i dont like hour and a half classes, especially when they're math, anthro and latin.  im having a weird day, in which one minute im all "gee, people are great and unique and wonderful and i love the earth" and then some person walks by and makes me IMPOSSIBLY angry because they are weird looking, or smoking, or just being stupid.  and there wwas like 100 people standing in the lobby outside of the library watching a car chase on tv... wtf?  it wasnt even on long island... if it was, then i would understand their interest.

sometimes, if i had to pick one word to describe myself, it would be awkward.  i hate that shit.  i am almost always super concious of stupid stuff that normal people probably dont even pay attention to.  like hands.  when im around people and i get nervous, i am so aware of myself, to the point of obsession.  ie, where do i put my hands? do i fold them? do i place them casually on the table or on my lap?  what the hell, who even cares?  me.  i always feel like people who like me will eventually realize that im not funny, im not nice, theres nothing special about me that should keep them liking me.  why do i think like that?  sometimes i feel like people have expectations of me that im not gonna be able to live up to and then they're not going to like me anymore.  i need to grow up.  this is not cool

what is even going on.  i couldnt tell you.  im having an overwhelming sense of forgetable-ness.  im certain thats not a real word, but i dont care, it defines me.  i miss high school and i miss people.  i really do.  college is too "grown up" for me.  i dont feel like i fit in with these people. i didnt feel like i fit in in high school either, but at least there i had friends.  i dont even feel like finishing this. everyone sucks. seriously.  YOU ALL SUCK.  THANKS!!!!

it is the weirdest feeling when you can pinpoint the second your feelings change.  but it doesnt last, because they always change back.  i think one of the best feelings is being calm and focused.  too bad it doesnt happen that often.  if i could be calm about things and have normal emotions and emotional reactions for the rest of my life.. that would be really cool.  the thought of going to sleep is making me really happy.  i love that.

i feel like im stuck and i cant breathe and i feel awkward. everything and everyone is annoying me and i dont want to look anyone in the eye. 

i only write in this when im in less than chipper moods; that doesnt mean its how i feel all the time.
school is lame <3

i spend my life waiting for something to happen, something to start, and it never does.

there are some people in life that have personalities that make people wanna kiss their ass, and then there are people that have no friends. i cant see how thats fair. but, i dont remember anyone ever saying life was going to be fair.

sometimes im allowed to be in a bad mood. it happens, more than anyone will ever realize.

i havent had real friends that i was entirely comfortable with since 8th grade, and im now a freshman in college.

i want people to miss me and i know they dont, and that makes me feel really small.

i wish i even knew someone to have a crush on. but i dont know anyone.

something isnt right and i dont know im ever going to be able to fix it. i think it might be a little too late.

my luck keeps flucuating.  one minute i drop my phone, and it totally comes apart, keys, wallet on to the wet ground and walk into a puddle, and the next i make almost every single light home.

when people send me chain letters on facebook, a chain letters that i have been getting since 6th grade, and those people dont even talk to me in real life, it tends to aggitate me.

when i ask someone about homework and they reply really snottily, it makes me cry because im a baby.  lately everything has been making me cry.

sometimes i feel like i dont have any emotions. that statement would negate the previous one, so obviously im a flip flopper too.

sometimes i dont want to be anywhere.

i dont like dramatic people.  i dont like people who lie and make shit up, then stry to be nonchalant to, i dont know, make themselves look cooler or something? i dont know, but i dont like it.  dont make up stories, dont try to up people, dont play the martyr because its transparent.  sometimes life isnt that serious, and stuff is not such a big deal.  just relax.  oh lordy i bet i sound bitter but im not, im just saying stuff.  who even cares.  also, why are some people so rude?  i dont get mad easily, i really dont.  dealing with people at work thati dont know, im nice to everyone, but come on.  dont come in and act like im stupid just because you are not clearly telling me your problem.  THAT pisses me off.

im at work and i cant really read what im writing because the font is teeny tiny on this computer.  yesterday i went to the mall with devon and it was a grand time.  i bought a t shirt that was probably too much money than it should have been, but it was from urban so duh, its gonna be overpriced.  then i saw shoes i really wanted, but apparently, textbooks have priority, so that purchase will be saved for another day.  i have nothing to say, im just updating for the sake of updating.  tata.

basically, i saw alot of movies over vacation.  meet the fockers was funny, darkness was stu[id, closer was redundant but good, and some other ones i forget but White Noise, holy moly, freak me out.  scary stuff.  i will not be putting the tv or radio on static channels ever in my life.   idont wanna mess with evp crap.  but go see it, because its good... the newspaper didnt give it any stars, but i think it deserved some.  UGH SCARY.

the semester is very much over; school, work, everything and christmas is in a few days which is wonderful because i love christmas, but its not the same this year.  devon's xanga put my in a reflective mood, domino effect.  and its weird because just the other day i was reading livejournals and was like geez, why does everything always need to be so dramatic and reflective, and now here i go.  but anyway, this year just isnt the same as last year.  because i can remember last year so vividly, especially around this time.  i remember the dumb survey i took on christmas eve and how i was having a conversation with keith, one of the first that made me realize what a good guy he is, even if i give him a hard time.  and that just makes me think about people and friends in general.  just how my head has been fucked up since i can remember, and senior year was the first time since grammar school that i really started to actively make friends and put real effort into them.  and what awesome people i picked.  obviously some of these friendships didnt turn out to be so spectacular as i originally thought, but thats ok, im dealing with that.  im not stupid, i do know that you have lives and i know that you cant drop everything to talk to me and that is by no means what i have ever been asking for.  im not a confrontational person with my friends, i dont like fights so im gonna try not to have them, and its not cool that when i try to hint at something, just because thats how i do it, you get defensive and then never talk to me again after i apologize.  but thats life.  im not gonna let it kill me.  its just sad that i look at my buddy list and could delete 3/4 of it and it wouldnt even matter.  i bet i sound like a broken record because every time i write and entry with any substance this is what its about but whatever, this is my drama right now.  and its not even that. this post is in NO WAY being like, accusing to people. im not mad anymore. so dont take it that way whoever happens to read this garbage.  im ok by myself for now.  i am, but we'll see what happens tomorrow. ha. anyway lets move on a little bit.

that santa thing was pretty cute.  it kinda sucked to be standing for hours at a time, but its nice to see little kids so excited.  it makes me miss being little and believing in santa.  buttt i suppose we all have to grow up eventually. i lost my train of thought so im done.  i get distracted way too easily.

we watched a movie in history today about civil rights and how it started and all that.  white people sucked.  there was a story on the movie about a 14 year old boy named Emmet Till.  i remember learning about that but not the way they showed it in the movie.  so this black boy was 14 and from the north and he was showing these other boys a picture of these white girls who were his girlfriends or something, so they told him to go talk to the white lady in the store, so he said bye baby.  then that night, the ladies husband and brother in law took the kid and killed him.  the beat him and shot him and tied him to a tractor peice and threw him in a river.  on the movie they showed the boys funeral, his mother wanted the casket kept open so everyone could see what the white guys did to her son.  it was disgusting.  it didnt look like a human being and i felt like a big nerd, but i had tears in my eyes.   then, of course, the men were found not guilty.  a few months later, a reporter paied them 4,000 to tell their story and they admitted all killing him and all the other terrible stuff they did to him.   yup.  that was my class for the day.  sick stuff.
